column1: Baby Barnaby's////It's nothing foodie or crazy creative
column2: but the breakfast hits the spot--and the prices are reasonable.  All of the dishes are pretty much classic breakfast hits
column3: with a bit of a Texas twist (of course!): French toast
column5: etc.  The French toast was cooked perfectly
column6: but I wasn't a huge fan of the chicken apple sausage.  A good spot for breakfast
column7: but just know that they fill up fast--at 8:15 on a Saturday morning
column8: the inside of the restaurant was entirely full
column9: and only a couple of tables outside were open.
